com.i2group.apollo.events.transport

Class PropertyChangeSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.events.transport.PropertyChangeSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IChangeSet<PropertyChange,Property>

    public final class PropertyChangeSet
extends Object
implements IChangeSet<PropertyChange,Property>
    Contains information about Propertys to be added to, changed in, or removed from a Card on an Item. Some commands restrict which of these lists can be populated.

    A PropertyChangeSet can contain zero or more new Propertys, zero or more PropertyChanges, and zero or more identifiers of Propertys to be removed.

    Validation:

    • The identifiers of new Propertys must be unique in their enclosing Item.
    • The identifiers of Propertys must not be empty.
    • The identifiers of Propertys must not exceed the maximum permitted length of 36 bytes.
    In addition, it is invalid for a card change set that adds a card to an item to contain a property change set that describes changed or removed properties.

    When you amend an existing card, you are free to add, change, and remove the properties and property groups that it contains. In this situation, there are no restrictions on the contents of property change sets that the card change set contains.

    Since:
    1.0
